HEADWORD: Conhydrine
<hw>Con*hy"drine</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ <?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Con</ets>ium + <ets>hydr</ets>ate.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A vegetable alkaloid found with conine in the poison hemlock
(<spn>Conium maculatum</spn>). It is a white crystalline substance,
<chform>C8H17NO</chform>, easily convertible into conine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

